com.paypal.merchant.sdk

Interface TransactionManager.PaymentResponse

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    TransactionManager.ChipAndPinAuthResponse
    Enclosing interface:
    TransactionManager

    public static interface TransactionManager.PaymentResponse
    When making a finalizePayment call you'll eventually receive a response. This is the object that is returned. It contains an error code (which might simply be Success) as well as a TransactionRecord which contains everything to know about this transaction.

    In future SDK releases the PaymentResponse may have new objects added to it besides the TransactionRecord. For that reason we don't use a TransactionRecord directly in the finalizePayment response.

    • Method Detail

      • getTransactionRecord

        TransactionRecord getTransactionRecord()
        Gets the TransactionRecord for this transaction. The TransactionRecord holds information such as the correlationId, transactionId, shopping cart used in the transaction, amounts, dates associated with the transaction, etc.
        Returns:
        A TransactionRecord object.

      • getIsSignatureRequiredToFinalize

        boolean getIsSignatureRequiredToFinalize()
        Is a signature required to finalize this transaction? If TRUE then the app should supply a signature image using the finalizePaymentForTransaction call

        Factors that influence this boolean include the Merchant's payment limits and the flag, which can be different per merchant, which indicates what amount over which a signature is required. (See Merchant.getPaymentLimits().getSignatureRequiredAbove())

        Also, for EMV readers, the card reader or the chip on the card may decide that a signature is required for this transaction.

        Returns:
        TRUE if a signature is required.
